criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Aneurysmal subarachnoid hemorrhage (aSAH), traumatic brain injury (TBI), acute deficiency
        Blood stroke (AIS), acute cerebral hemorrhage (ICH), hypoxic ischemic encephalopathy (HIE),
        Sepsis-associated encephalopathy (SAE), intracranial tumor surgery; older than 18 years
        old, <85 Years old; patients who need lumbar puncture.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Age <18 years old;

          2. Pregnancy;

          3. The condition of the temporal window is limited and the image cannot be obtained;

          4. The frequency spectrum of bilateral cerebral arteries shows stenosis;

          5. Patients with cerebral artery stenosis

          6. Patients who have not obtained informed consent;
